{
  "texts": [
    "This corresponds to a field oscillation frequency of log 10 (f /Hz) ≈ -8.3, which is consistent with the CGW candidate examined in EPTA Collaboration & InPTA Collaboration (2023c).",
    "When a joint ULDM+GWB search is performed, however, the peak in the ULDM mass posterior distribution vanishes, as the data strongly prefer the presence of an HD correlation in the common power.",
    "We therefore conclude that an ULDM origin of the detected signal is disfavoured, placing a direct constraint on the abundance of ULDM in our Galaxy.",
    "The non-detection in DR2new implies that only about 80% of the DM density in the solar neighbourhood can be attributed to ULDM with -24 < log 10 (m φ /eV) < -23.7.",
    "More stringent constraints are obtained from DR2full and are presented in a separate paper (Smarra et al. 2023)."
  ]
}